The paper deals with revenue maximization in selling multiple goods, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and economics (cs.EC). The use of duality theory techniques suggests a mathematical optimization approach, which falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and mathematical optimization (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the performance of deterministic and randomized selling mechanisms, which involves analyzing the information-theoretic properties of the valuations (cs.IT).
